div1.p:
Samuel Dexter
depos'd, On Saturday the 29th of November, the Prisoners and I met near the Bull-Head in Jewin-Street, and then went out and Robb'd Mr. Warwick; we took from him 18 s. 6 d. in Money, and a pair of Shoes;
Thomas Rogers
held the Pistol, and I took the Shoes out of his Bosom, and the Money out of his Pocket, then went to the Gentleman and Porter and shar'd it; there was four half Crowns, and 8 s. 6 d. in small Silver;
Richard Rogers
had the Shoes, and allow'd us twelve pence a-piece for them; on the 5th of December I discover'd it to Mr. Willis, and we were to have gone out that Night.
